# .clinerules — Cline Operational Rules

## Session Start (do this before any work)
1. Read memory-bank files in full
2. Read AGENTS.md in full
3. Confirm active task with the user before writing any code

## Session End (do this before closing)
1. Update memory bank with any new decisions, patterns, or gotchas discovered
2. If a bug was found in a protected file, add it to BACKLOG.md instead of editing

## MCP Server Usage

### MCPunk — use before editing existing code
- Before modifying any existing function or class, use MCPunk to search
  for related functions, usages, and dependents first
- Do not read entire files when MCPunk can retrieve the relevant chunk

### Context7 — use before writing code that touches any external library
- Always fetch current docs for: Playwright, Streamlit, pytest, uv, ruff, mypy
- Do not rely on training knowledge for library APIs — it may be outdated

### Memory Bank — use for project state, not code
- Store: architecture decisions, settled conventions, known gotchas, session outcomes
- Do not store: code snippets, file contents, anything already in AGENTS.md
- Prune stale entries — outdated memory actively causes mistakes

## General Discipline
- One feature per session (see AGENTS.md §10)
- Never declare work done without running end-to-end
- Always: ruff → mypy → pytest → human reviews diff → then commit